						               													<description>A cooperative children's game using the popular theme of &amp;quot;kuflik&amp;quot; (amorph, more or less bean-shaped creatures in Hungarian kids' books). Each play starts with a story - one of the &amp;quot;kufli&amp;quot;s loses something (there are 16 stories included in the box) and players have to find out which creature of the meadow took it. For this they walk around the meadow, trying to find certain creatures (shown on face-down tiles) that remember something about the animal (like &amp;quot;It didn't have fur... I'm allergic to fur and I wasn't sneezing.&amp;quot;). After four main features are known, players find out who the thief is and try to remember where that thief is on the board. If they succeed, they've won!&amp;#10;&amp;#10;3 game variants are included in the box:&amp;#10;- from age 3: no memory element - tiles that have been turned up remain face-up&amp;#10;- from age 4: cooperative play&amp;#10;- from age 6: competitive play with players holding certain creatures' cards in hand, sometimes drawing from each other and trying to have the thief in hand in the end.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
